sentence: Central Garden & Pet CompanyCENT is slated to report first-quarter fiscal 2016 results on Feb 2.
The big question facing investors is, whether this producer and marketer of lawn & garden products and pet supplies will be able to deliver a positive earnings surprise in the quarter to be reported.
In the trailing four quarters, the company outperformed the Zacks Consensus Estimate by an average of 50.4%.
Let's see how things are shaping up for this announcement.
Our proven model does not conclusively show that Central Garden & Pet is likely to beat estimates this quarter.
This is because a stock needs to have both a positive Earnings ESP and a Zacks Rank #1, 2 or 3 for this to happen.
Central Garden & Pet has an Earnings ESP of 0.00% as the Most Accurate estimate and the Zacks Consensus Estimate both stand at a loss of 12 cents.
The company carries a Zacks Rank #1 (Strong Buy), which increases the predictive power of ESP.
However, the company's ESP of 0.00% makes surprise prediction difficult.
Central Garden & Pet is revamping both its Pet and Garden segments.
The company intends to have a balanced approach that encompasses improvement in both the top and bottom lines through operational efficiency and targeted acquisitions.
However, analysts remain concerned about the softness in grass seed as well as dÃ©cor revenue that weighed upon the company's performance in the fourth quarter.
For the first quarter of fiscal 2016, the company expects earnings to be flat on a year-over-year basis, primarily due to revenue timing differences.
